# Public-repo policy
# ------------------
# Only the README, this .gitignore, and the notebooks/ directory are tracked.
# Everything else — project-management notes (meta/), source skeletons (src/),
# literature notes, drafts, scripts, scaffold — stays local-only.
#
# To track an additional path, add an explicit `!/path` line below.

# Ignore every top-level entry by default.
/*

# Allow these.
!/.gitignore
!/README.md
!/notebooks/
!/requirements.txt
!/.env.example
!/RUNNING.md

# Track the remote dataset-generation runner + its SLURM wrapper, but keep the
# rest of scripts/ (notebook builders, watchers) local-only. Re-include the dir,
# re-ignore its contents, then allow-list just these two files.
!/scripts/
/scripts/*
!/scripts/generate_dataset.py
!/scripts/extract_features.py
!/scripts/run_generate_dataset.sbatch
!/scripts/setup_pod.sh
!/scripts/push_results.sh
!/scripts/test_run.sh

# Track the small TEXT dataset (stories / prompts / spec / manifests) so the repo
# is self-contained, but keep large BINARY feature arrays out (→ HF Hub / wandb).
!/data/
/data/*
!/data/processed/
*.npz
*.npy
*.h5
*.hdf5

# Inside the allow-listed dirs, still ignore the usual junk.
notebooks/.ipynb_checkpoints/
notebooks/**/.ipynb_checkpoints/
